question: Points A and B are 70 km apart on a highway. A car starts from A and another car starts from B at the same time. If they travel in the same direction, they meet in 7 hours, but if they travel towards each other they meet in one hour. What are their respective speeds?

Fact_Diagram:

    D --> D1[Meet in 1 hour]
Answer_Reasoning: Let the speed of the car from point A be x km/h and the speed of the car from point B be y km/h. <C>When the cars travel in the same direction, their relative speed is the difference of their speeds</C>, which is (x-y) km/h. <C1>They meet in 7 hours and cover a distance of 70 km. Using the formula distance = speed  time, we have 7(x-y) = <B1>70</B1></C1>, which simplifies to x - y = 10. <D>When the cars travel towards each other, their relative speed is the sum of their speeds</D>, which is (x+y) km/h. <D1>They meet in 1 hour, covering a distance of 70 km. Therefore, 1(x+y) = <B1>70</B1></D1>, which simplifies to x + y = 70. Now we have two equations: x - y = 10 and x + y = 70. Solving these equations simultaneously, we get x = 40 and y = 30. Therefore, the speed of the car that starts from A is 40 km/h and the speed of the car that starts from B is 30 km/h. 
Final_Answer: {40, 30}
